<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n20231a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n20" href="#n20231a">N20 (VI.B.13)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n20all.htm#n20231a"> 231(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> secretary, author in Eter</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">In July of the same year <font color="green">[1803]</font>, in another letter to Butts, he wrote: &ldquo;I hope &hellip; to speak to future generations by a sublime allegory, which is now perfectly completed into a grand poem. I may praise it, since I dare not pretend to be any other than the secretary; the authors are in eternity&rdquo; <small> Darrell Figgis, <a name="DFPW" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#DFPW"><cite title="source">The Paintings of William Blake</cite></a> (1925) 52</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
